{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848402023,"sessionID":"ses_2873001a1ffe1HZzyFzQGSya52","part":{"id":"prt_d78d027df001ZbIlZJQkJqbwZb","messageID":"msg_d78d01ef10018aaYhq4TtYHuHV","sessionID":"ses_2873001a1ffe1HZzyFzQGSya52","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d85a8bd425414a7bb1ada9c665d64b96","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"time\"\n6: \n7: \tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n8: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n9: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n10: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n11: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n12: \n13: \twmTypes \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n14: \n15: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n16: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n17: )\n18: \n19: var (\n20: \tSandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n21: \t\tGroup:    \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n22: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n23: \t\tResource: \"sandboxes\",\n24: \t}\n25: \n26: \tSandboxClaimGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{\n27: \t\tGroup:    \"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\",\n28: \t\tVersion:  \"v1alpha1\",\n29: \t\tResource: \"sandboxclaims\",\n30: \t}\n31: )\n32: \n33: type GarbageCollector struct {\n34: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n35: \tstoreClient   store.Store\n36: \tinterval      time.Duration\n37: \tctx           context.Context\n38: \tcancel        context.CancelFunc\n39: }\n40: \n41: func NewGarbageCollector(\n42: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface,\n43: \tstoreClient store.Store,\n44: \tinterval time.Duration,\n45: ) *GarbageCollector {\n46: \tctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n47: \treturn &GarbageCollector{\n48: \t\tdynamicClient: dynamicClient,\n49: \t\tstoreClient:   storeClient,\n50: \t\tinterval:      interval,\n51: \t\tctx:           ctx,\n52: \t\tcancel:        cancel,\n53: \t}\n54: }\n55: \n56: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Start() {\n57: \tgo gc.gcLoop()\n58: }\n59: \n60: func (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop() {\n61: \tgc.cancel()\n62: }\n63: \n64: func (gc *GarbageCollector) gcLoop() {\n65: \tticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)\n66: \tdefer ticker.Stop()\n67: \n68: \tklog.Info(\"GarbageCollector started\")\n69: \n70: \tfor {\n71: \t\tselect {\n72: \t\tcase <-gc.ctx.Done():\n73: \t\t\tklog.Info(\"GarbageCollector stopped\")\n74: \t\t\treturn\n75: \t\tcase <-ticker.C:\n76: \t\t\tgc.tick()\n77: \t\t}\n78: \t}\n79: }\n80: \n81: func (gc *GarbageCollector) tick() {\n82: \ttickCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(gc.ctx, GCSingleTickTimeout)\n83: \tdefer cancel()\n84: \n85: \tnow := time.Now()\n86: \tidleThreshold := now.Add(-DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)\n87: \texpiredThreshold := now\n88: \n89: \tidleSandboxes, err := gc.storeClient.ListInactiveSandboxes(tickCtx, idleThreshold, 16)\n90: \tif err != nil {\n91: \t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to list inactive sandboxes: %v\", err)\n92: \t} else {\n93: \t\tfor _, sandbox := range idleSandboxes {\n94: \t\t\tgc.deleteSandbox(tickCtx, sandbox, wmTypes.CleanupReasonIdleTimeout)\n95: \t\t}\n96: \t}\n97: \n98: \texpiredSandboxes, err := gc.storeClient.ListExpiredSandboxes(tickCtx, expiredThreshold, 16)\n99: \tif err != nil {\n100: \t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to list expired sandboxes: %v\", err)\n101: \t} else {\n102: \t\tfor _, sandbox := range expiredSandboxes {\n103: \t\t\tgc.deleteSandbox(tickCtx, sandbox, wmTypes.CleanupReasonExpired)\n104: \t\t}\n105: \t}\n106: }\n107: \n108: func (gc *GarbageCollector) deleteSandbox(\n109: \tctx context.Context,\n110: \tsandbox *types.SandboxInfo,\n111: \treason wmTypes.SandboxCleanupReason,\n112: ) {\n113: \tauditEntry := &wmTypes.CleanupAuditEntry{\n114: \t\tSessionID: sandbox.SessionID,\n115: \t\tSandboxID: sandbox.SandboxID,\n116: \t\tNamespace: sandbox.SandboxNamespace,\n117: \t\tReason:    reason,\n118: \t\tDeletedAt: time.Now(),\n119: \t}\n120: \n121: \tgvr := SandboxGVR\n122: \tif sandbox.Kind == \"SandboxClaim\" {\n123: \t\tgvr = SandboxClaimGVR\n124: \t}\n125: \n126: \tdeleteCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, DeleteTimeout)\n127: \tdefer cancel()\n128: \n129: \terr := gc.dynamicClient.Resource(gvr).\n130: \t\tNamespace(sandbox.SandboxNamespace).\n131: \t\tDelete(deleteCtx, sandbox.SandboxID, metav1.DeleteOptions{})\n132: \n133: \tif err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n134: \t\tauditEntry.ErrorMessage = err.Error()\n135: \t\tauditEntry.Success = false\n136: \t\tklog.Errorf(\"Failed to delete sandbox %s/%s: %v\", sandbox.SandboxNamespace, sandbox.SandboxID, err)\n137: \t} else {\n138: \t\tif err := gc.storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sandbox.SessionID); err != nil {\n139: \t\t\tklog.Warningf(\"Failed to delete sandbox %s from store: %v\", sandbox.SessionID, err)\n140: \t\t}\n141: \t\tauditEntry.Success = true\n142: \t\tklog.Infof(\"Deleted sandbox %s/%s (reason: %s)\", sandbox.SandboxNamespace, sandbox.SandboxID, reason)\n143: \t}\n144: \n145: \tgc.recordAudit(auditEntry)\n146: }\n147: \n148: func (gc *GarbageCollector) recordAudit(entry *wmTypes.CleanupAuditEntry) {\n149: \tklog.Infof(\"Cleanup audit: sessionId=%s sandboxId=%s namespace=%s reason=%s success=%v deletedAt=%s\",\n150: \t\tentry.SessionID, entry.SandboxID, entry.Namespace, entry.Reason, entry.Success, entry.DeletedAt.Format(time.RFC3339))\n151: \tif entry.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n152: \t\tklog.Infof(\"Cleanup audit error: %s\", entry.ErrorMessage)\n153: \t}\n154: }\n\n(End of file - total 154 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n\t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n\n\twmTypes \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/types\"\n\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tSandboxGVR = schema.GroupVersionResource{","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go","time":{"start":1775848401993,"end":1775848402021}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848402025,"sessionID":"ses_2873001a1ffe1HZzyFzQGSya52","part":{"id":"prt_d78d02a0b001QEcMShrON6eU2o","messageID":"msg_d78d01ef10018aaYhq4TtYHuHV","sessionID":"ses_2873001a1ffe1HZzyFzQGSya52","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bdbb60ddb534470b936377e133b0e339","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design-gc.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design-gc.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: **AR**: AR-008  \n4: **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n5: **Language**: Go  \n6: **Size**: S  \n7: **Purpose**: Implement periodic garbage collection for sandbox resources based on idle timeout and TTL expiry.\n8: \n9: ## Architecture\n10: \n11: ### Component Overview\n12: \n13: ```\n14: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n15: │                     WorkloadManager                         │\n16: │                                                              │\n17: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n18: │  │              GarbageCollector                        │  │\n19: │  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐     │  │\n20: │  │  │ gcLoop()   │  │ tick()     │  │ deleteSandbox() │  │  │\n21: │  │  │ (ticker)   │  │ (timeout)  │  │ (K8s API + Store) │ │\n22: │  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘     │  │\n23: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n24: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n25:          │                        │\n26:          │                        │\n27:          ▼                        ▼\n28: ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n29: │  Kubernetes API  │  │     Redis Store  │\n30: │  (Sandbox CRDs)  │  │  (Session Data)  │\n31: └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### Cleanup Triggers\n35: \n36: 1. **Idle Timeout**: Sandboxes with `LastActivityAt < now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15 minutes)\n37: 2. **TTL Expiry**: Sandboxes with `ExpiresAt < now`\n38: 3. **Manual Deletion**: Explicit session deletion via API\n39: \n40: ## Data Structures\n41: \n42: ### GarbageCollector\n43: \n44: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n45: \n46: ```go\n47: type GarbageCollector struct {\n48: \tdynamicClient dynamic.Interface  // Kubernetes dynamic client for CRD operations\n49: \tstoreClient   store.Store        // Redis store for session data\n50: \tinterval      time.Duration      // GC run interval (default: 15s)\n51: \tctx           context.Context    // Context for cancellation\n52: \tcancel        context.CancelFunc // Cancel function for graceful shutdown\n53: }\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ### Cleanup Reasons\n57: \n58: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go`\n59: \n60: ```go\n61: type SandboxCleanupReason string\n62: \n63: const (\n64: \tCleanupReasonManual      SandboxCleanupReason = \"manual\"\n65: \tCleanupReasonIdleTimeout SandboxCleanupReason = \"idle_timeout\"\n66: \tCleanupReasonExpired     SandboxCleanupReason = \"expired\"\n67: )\n68: ```\n69: \n70: ### Audit Entry\n71: \n72: ```go\n73: type CleanupAuditEntry struct {\n74: \tSessionID    string               `json:\"sessionId\"`\n75: \tSandboxID    string               `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n76: \tNamespace    string               `json:\"namespace\"`\n77: \tReason       SandboxCleanupReason `json:\"reason\"`\n78: \tDeletedAt    time.Time            `json:\"deletedAt\"`\n79: \tSuccess      bool                 `json:\"success\"`\n80: \tErrorMessage string               `json:\"errorMessage,omitempty\"`\n81: }\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ## API Contracts\n85: \n86: ### Kubernetes CRD Resources\n87: \n88: The GarbageCollector operates on two CRD types:\n89: \n90: | GVR | Group | Version | Resource |\n91: |-----|-------|---------|----------|\n92: | `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes` | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `sandboxes` |\n93: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxclaims` | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `sandboxclaims` |\n94: \n95: ### Store Interface\n96: \n97: ```go\n98: type Store interface {\n99: \t// ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes with ExpiresAt < before\n100: \tListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n101: \t\n102: \t// ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes with LastActivityAt < before\n103: \tListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n104: \t\n105: \t// DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session data from Redis\n106: \tDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n107: }\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### SandboxInfo (from Store)\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: type SandboxInfo struct {\n114: \tSessionID           string    `json:\"sessionId\"`\n115: \tSandboxID           string    `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n116: \tSandboxNamespace    string    `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n117: \tKind                string    `json:\"kind\"` // \"Sandbox\" or \"SandboxClaim\"\n118: \tExpiresAt           time.Time `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n119: \tLastActivityAt      time.Time `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n120: }\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ## Error Handling\n124: \n125: ### Error Scenarios\n126: \n127: | Scenario | Handling |\n128: |----------|----------|\n129: | Store query fails | Log error, continue to next query |\n130: | K8s API delete fails (NotFound) | Treat as success, delete from store |\n131: | K8s API delete fails (other) | Log error, audit as failure, continue |\n132: | Store delete fails | Log warning (not critical) |\n133: | Context timeout | Cancel current tick, retry next interval |\n134: \n135: ### Error Logging\n136: \n137: All errors are logged with structured fields:\n138: - Session ID\n139: - Sandbox ID\n140: - Namespace\n141: - Reason\n142: - Error message\n143: \n144: ## Testing Strategy\n145: \n146: ### Unit Tests\n147: \n148: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n149: \n150: ```go\n151: package workloadmanager_test\n152: \n153: import (\n154: \t\"context\"\n155: \t\"testing\"\n156: \t\"time\"\n157: \n158: \t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n159: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n160: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n161: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema\"\n162: \tdynamicfake \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n163: \n164: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n165: )\n166: \n167: var _ = Describe(\"GarbageCollector\", func() {\n168: \tvar (\n169: \t\tfakeDynamicClient *dynamicfake.FakeDynamicClient\n170: \t\tfakeStore         *FakeStore\n171: \t\tgc                *workloadmanager.GarbageCollector\n172: \t\tctx               context.Context\n173: \t)\n174: \n175: \tBeforeEach(func() {\n176: \t\tscheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n177: \t\tfakeDynamicClient = dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n178: \t\tfakeStore = NewFakeStore()\n179: \t\tgc = workloadmanager.NewGarbageCollector(fakeDynamicClient, fakeStore, 100*time.Millisecond)\n180: \t\tctx = context.Background()\n181: \t})\n182: \n183: \tAfterEach(func() {\n184: \t\tgc.Stop()\n185: \t})\n186: \n187: \tContext(\"Cleanup of idle sandboxes\", func() {\n188: \t\tIt(\"should delete sandboxes idle for more than timeout\", func() {\n189: \t\t\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n190: \t\t\t\tSessionID:        \"test-session\",\n191: \t\t\t\tSandboxID:        \"test-sandbox\",\n192: \t\t\t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n193: \t\t\t\tKind:             \"Sandbox\",\n194: \t\t\t\tExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(1 * time.Hour),\n195: \t\t\t\tLastActivityAt:   time.Now().Add(-20 * time.Minute),\n196: \t\t\t}\n197: \t\t\tfakeStore.AddSandbox(sandbox)\n198: \n199: \t\t\tgc.Start()\n200: \t\t\ttime.Sleep(200 * time.Millisecond)\n201: \n202: \t\t\tEventually(func() bool {\n203: \t\t\t\treturn fakeStore.IsDeleted(\"test-session\")\n204: \t\t\t}).Should(BeTrue())\n205: \t\t})\n206: \t})\n207: \n208: \tContext(\"Cleanup of expired sandboxes\", func() {\n209: \t\tIt(\"should delete sandboxes past their TTL\", func() {\n210: \t\t\tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n211: \t\t\t\tSessionID:        \"test-session\",\n212: \t\t\t\tSandboxID:        \"test-sandbox\",\n213: \t\t\t\tSandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n214: \t\t\t\tKind:             \"Sandbox\",\n215: \t\t\t\tExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour),\n216: \t\t\t\tLastActivityAt:   time.Now(),\n217: \t\t\t}\n218: \t\t\tfakeStore.AddSandbox(sandbox)\n219: \n220: \t\t\tgc.Start()\n221: \t\t\ttime.Sleep(200 * time.Millisecond)\n222: \n223: \t\t\tEventually(func() bool {\n224: \t\t\t\treturn fakeStore.IsDeleted(\"test-session\")\n225: \t\t\t}).Should(BeTrue())\n226: \t\t})\n227: \t})\n228: \n229: \tContext(\"Error handling\", func() {\n230: \t\tIt(\"should continue on store errors\", func() {\n231: \t\t\tfakeStore.FailOnQuery = true\n232: \n233: \t\t\tgc.Start()\n234: \t\t\ttime.Sleep(200 * time.Millisecond)\n235: \n236: \t\t\tExpect(fakeStore.QueryCount).To(BeNumerically(\">\", 0))\n237: \t\t})\n238: \t})\n239: })\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ### Integration Tests\n243: \n244: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_gc_test.go`\n245: \n246: ```go\n247: package workloadmanager_test\n248: \n249: import (\n250: \t\"context\"\n251: \t\"testing\"\n252: \t\"time\"\n253: \n254: \t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n255: \t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n256: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n257: \t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/envtest\"\n258: \n259: \t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n260: )\n261: \n262: var _ = Describe(\"GarbageCollector Integration\", func() {\n263: \tvar (\n264: \t\tenvTest *envtest.Environment\n265: \t\tgc      *workloadmanager.GarbageCollector\n266: \t)\n267: \n268: \tBeforeSuite(func() {\n269: \t\tenvTest = &envtest.Environment{\n270: \t\t\tCRDDirectoryPaths: []string{\"../../manifests/charts/base/crds\"},\n271: \t\t}\n272: \n273: \t\tcfg, err := envTest.Start()\n274: \t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n275: \n276: \t\tdynamicClient, err := dynamic.NewForConfig(cfg)\n277: \t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n278: \n279: \t\tstore, err := store.NewRedisStore(...)\n280: \t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n281: \n282: \t\tgc = workloadmanager.NewGarbageCollector(dynamicClient, store, 15*time.Second)\n283: \t\tgc.Start()\n284: \t})\n285: \n286: \tAfterSuite(func() {\n287: \t\tgc.Stop()\n288: \t\terr := envTest.Stop()\n289: \t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n290: \t})\n291: \n292: \tIt(\"should cleanup real sandbox resources\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n293: \t\tsessionID := \"integration-test-session\"\n294: \t\t\n295: \t\terr := store.CreateSession(ctx, sessionID, &store.SessionMetadata{\n296: \t\t\tExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(-1 * time.Hour),\n297: \t\t\tLastActivity: time.Now(),\n298: \t\t}, 0)\n299: \t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n300: \n301: \t\tEventually(func() bool {\n302: \t\t\t_, err := store.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)\n303: \t\t\treturn err != nil\n304: \t\t}, 30*time.Second, time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n305: \t}, SpecTimeout(60*time.Second))\n306: })\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ## Configuration\n310: \n311: ### Default Constants\n312: \n313: **File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n314: \n315: ```go\n316: const (\n317: \tDefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour\n318: \tDefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n319: \tGCInterval                = 15 * time.Second\n320: \tGCSingleTickTimeout       = 2 * time.Minute\n321: \tDeleteTimeout             = 30 * time.Second\n322: \tBatchSize                 = 16\n323: )\n324: ```\n325: \n326: ### Configuration Options\n327: \n328: | Option | Type | Default | Description |\n329: |--------|------|---------|-------------|\n330: | `Session.DefaultTimeout` | `time.Duration` | `15m` | Idle timeout for cleanup |\n331: | `Session.MaxDuration` | `time.Duration` | `8h` | Maximum session TTL |\n332: | `Session.CleanupInterval` | `time.Duration` | `15s` | GC run interval |\n333: \n334: ## Metrics\n335: \n336: ### Prometheus Metrics\n337: \n338: ```go\n339: const (\n340: \tmetricGCRunsTotal           = \"workloadmanager_gc_runs_total\"\n341: \tmetricGCDeletedSandboxes    = \"workloadmanager_gc_deleted_sandboxes_total\"\n342: \tmetricGCDeletionFailures    = \"workloadmanager_gc_deletion_failures_total\"\n343: \tmetricGCTickDuration        = \"workloadmanager_gc_tick_duration_seconds\"\n344: )\n345: \n346: var (\n347: \tgcRunsTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n348: \t\tprometheus.CounterOpts{\n349: \t\t\tName: metricGCRunsTotal,\n350: \t\t\tHelp: \"Total number of GC runs\",\n351: \t\t},\n352: \t\t[]string{\"reason\"},\n353: \t)\n354: \n355: \tgcDeletedSandboxes = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n356: \t\tprometheus.CounterOpts{\n357: \t\t\tName: metricGCDeletedSandboxes,\n358: \t\t\tHelp: \"Total number of sandboxes deleted by GC\",\n359: \t\t},\n360: \t\t[]string{\"reason\", \"kind\"},\n361: \t)\n362: \n363: \tgcTickDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n364: \t\tprometheus.HistogramOpts{\n365: \t\t\tName:    metricGCTickDuration,\n366: \t\t\tHelp:    \"GC tick duration in seconds\",\n367: \t\t\tBuckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n368: \t\t},\n369: \t\t[]string{\"reason\"},\n370: \t)\n371: )\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ## Dependencies\n375: \n376: ### Go Module Dependencies\n377: \n378: ```go\n379: require (\n380: \tk8s.io/client-go v0.32.1  // dynamic.Interface for CRD operations\n381: \tgo-redis/v9 v9.7.0        // store.Store interface\n382: \tk8s.io/klog/v2 v2.130.1  // structured logging\n383: )\n384: ```\n385: \n386: ### Kubernetes RBAC\n387: \n388: ```yaml\n389: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n390: kind: ClusterRole\n391: metadata:\n392:   name: workloadmanager-gc\n393: rules:\n394: - apiGroups: [\"agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n395:   resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n396:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"delete\"]\n397: - apiGroups: [\"extensions.agents.x-k8s.io\"]\n398:   resources: [\"sandboxclaims\"]\n399:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"delete\"]\n400: ```\n401: \n402: ## Lifecycle Management\n403: \n404: ### Startup\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: // In server.go\n408: func (s *Server) Start() error {\n409: \t// ... other initialization\n410: \n411: \t// Start garbage collector\n412: \ts.garbageCollector = NewGarbageCollector(\n413: \t\ts.k8sClient.DynamicClient,\n414: \t\ts.store,\n415: \t\ts.config.Session.CleanupInterval,\n416: \t)\n417: \ts.garbageCollector.Start()\n418: \n419: \t// Start HTTP server\n420: \t// ...\n421: }\n422: ```\n423: \n424: ### Shutdown\n425: \n426: ```go\n427: func (s *Server) Stop() error {\n428: \ts.cancel()\n429: \n430: \t// Stop garbage collector\n431: \tif s.garbageCollector != nil {\n432: \t\ts.garbageCollector.Stop()\n433: \t}\n434: \n435: \t// Wait for goroutines\n436: \ts.wg.Wait()\n437: \n438: \treturn nil\n439: }\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ## Security Considerations\n443: \n444: 1. **RBAC Enforcement**: GC service account requires minimal permissions (delete only on sandbox resources)\n445: 2. **Namespace Isolation**: GC respects sandbox namespace boundaries\n446: 3. **Audit Logging**: All deletions are logged with session ID, sandbox ID, and reason\n447: 4. **Error Handling**: Partial failures don't affect other sandboxes\n448: \n449: ## Performance Characteristics\n450: \n451: | Metric | Value |\n452: |--------|-------|\n453: | GC Interval | 15 seconds |\n454: | Batch Size | 16 sandboxes per tick |\n455: | Single Tick Timeout | 2 minutes |\n456: | Delete Timeout | 30 seconds per sandbox |\n457: | Storage Overhead | O(n) where n = number of sessions |\n458: | API Load | ~1-2 req/s per 1000 active sessions |\n\n(End of file - total 458 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**AR**: AR-008  \n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language**: Go  \n**Size**: S  \n**Purpose**: Implement periodic garbage collection for sandbox resources based on idle timeout and TTL expiry.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     WorkloadManager                         │\n│                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │              GarbageCollector                        │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐     │  │\n│  │  │ gcLoop()   │  │ tick()     │  │ deleteSandbox() │  │  │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design-gc.md","time":{"start":1775848401996,"end":1775848402023}}}}
